EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Katz:
Pursuant to Rule 11.20 b of the Council and Section 20-225 (g) of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council resolves that the action of the Department of Consumer Affairs approving an enclosed sidewalk café located at 70-04 Austin Street, Community Board No. 6 20075075 TCQ, shall be subject to review by the Council.
EventItemMatterName: Concerning the petition of Piu Bello, Inc., to establish, maintain and operate an unenclosed sidewalk café located at 70-09 Austin Street, Queens (20075075TCQ).

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Mendez:
Pursuant to Rule 11.20 b of the Council and Section 20-225 (g) of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council resolves that the action of the Department of Consumer Affairs approving an enclosed sidewalk café located at 48 East 12th Street, Community Board No. 6 20065540 TCM, shall be subject to review by the Council.
EventItemMatterName: Petition of P12, Inc. d/b/a Piola, to establish, maintain and operate an unenclosed sidewalk café located at 48 East 12th Street, Manhattan. (20065540TCM)

INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to the office of emergency management.
EventItemMatterName: In relation to the office of emergency management.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene to issue an annual report detailing the health status and treatment of uniformed first responders who are registered with the World Trade Center Health Registry.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Dept of Health and Mental Hygiene to issue an annual report detailing the health status and treatment of uniformed first responders who are registered with the World Trade Center Health Registry.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of City Planning to file an application to amend the text of the Zoning Resolution in regard to language requirements on signs.
EventItemMatterName: Department of City Planning to file an application to amend the text of the Zoning Resolution in regard to language requirements on signs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Con Edison to remove all forms of footwear and other encumbrances from all phone and power lines in the city of New York to improve the safety and well-being of the residents of the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Con Edison to remove of all forms of footwear and other encumbrances from all phone and power lines in NYC to improve the safety and well-being of the residents of NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the disclosure of information regarding past engagement in slavery by city contractors.
EventItemMatterName: Disclosure of information regarding past engagement in slavery by city contractors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of counterfeit goods.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of counterfeit goods.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing a temporary commission to conduct a review of New York City’s child welfare system and offer recommendations for reform.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a temporary commission to conduct a review of NYC’s child welfare system and offer recommendations for reform.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to benefits pursuant to section four hundred twenty-one-a of the real property tax law.
EventItemMatterName: Benefits pursuant to section 421-a of the real property tax law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to priority queue status for alternative fuel taxicabs.
EventItemMatterName: Priority queue status for alternative fuel taxicabs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requirements for foundation and earthwork permits.
EventItemMatterName: Requirements for foundation and earthwork permits.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to act more swiftly in making the renovations, upgrades and repairs necessary to ensure that people with disabilities are able to fully utilize New York City’s subways, buses, stations and facilities, in the spirit of the 16th anniversary of the passage of the Americans With Disabilities Act.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to act more swiftly in making the renovations, upgrades and repairs necessary to ensure that people with disabilities are able to fully utilize NYC’s subways, buses, stations and facilities.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing the offense of unlawfully dealing with a minor by certain establishments.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing the offense of unlawfully dealing with a minor by certain establishments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Buildings to assess the merits of the use of plastic lining in pipes within buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Buildings to assess the merits of the use of plastic lining in pipes within buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign Assembly bill A.10944 sponsored by Assemblywoman Deborah Glick, in relation to the renewal of a Rent Stabilized lease and the definition of demolition in the context of the laws that apply to Rent Stabilization.
EventItemMatterName: The renewal of a Rent Stabilized lease and the definition of demolition in the context of the laws that apply to Rent Stabilization (A10944).

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to benchmarking the energy and water efficiency of buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Benchmarking the energy and water efficiency of buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: Resolution denouncing the Redux Beverage Company for producing, advertising, and distributing the “Cocaine” energy drink and calling for all local establishments to refuse to carry or sell “Cocaine” energy drink.
EventItemMatterName: Denouncing the Redux Beverage Company for producing, advertising, and distributing the “Cocaine” energy drink.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to annual inspection of and reporting on structural integrity in police precincts.
EventItemMatterName: Annual inspection of and reporting on structural integrity in police precincts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to annual inspection of and reporting on structural integrity in firehouse and emergency medical service stations.
EventItemMatterName: Annual inspection of and reporting on structural integrity in firehouse and emergency medical service stations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of meats.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of meats.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass S.1779/H.R.3931, the “Downed Animal Protection Act,” which would amend the Humane Methods of Livestock Slaughter Act of 1958 to ensure the humane slaughter of non-ambulatory livestock, thus preventing such meat from entering the human food supply.
EventItemMatterName: “Downed Animal Protection Act” (S.1779/H.R.3931)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Senate to introduce and pass legislation similar to Assembly Bill 10692, which would require insurance companies to cover policyholders’ dependents until the age of 25, regardless of enrollment in an educational institution.
EventItemMatterName: Require insurance companies to cover policyholders’ dependents until the age of 25, regardless of enrollment in an educational institution.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution designating the Speaker as the Council Member chosen by the Council to serve on the special committee to appoint the director of the City’s Independent Budget Office, in accordance with section 259 of the New York City Charter.
EventItemMatterName: Resolution designating the Speaker as the Council Member chosen by the Council to serve on the special committee to appoint the director of the City’s Independent Budget Office.
